Page: Steer, Don't Drift (steer.html)
Strategic Objective: To rebrand this page from a "User Manual" into a "Behavioral Compass". It serves as the cognitive guardrail against "Drift" and "Digital Decay," emphasizing that the human must control the psychology while AI handles the processing.

1. The Page Label & Subtitle Rebranding
We agreed to move away from mechanical/passive language toward "Operator" language.

The Change:

Label: From "THE NAVIGATION LAYER" to "THE BEHAVIORAL COMPASS".

Subtitle: From "The AI does the work. You choose the direction" to "AI handles the processing. You handle the Psychology.".

The Rationale:

"Navigation" sounds like following a map. "Compass" implies active judgment in unknown terrain.

Explicitly naming "Psychology" validates the EQ pillar, reinforcing that the human's role is to navigate Belief Systems and Hidden Drivers that the AI cannot see.

2. The "Sandhurst Influence" Integration (The Leader's Sphere)
We introduced a new section to weaponize your military training on Followership.

The Change:

New Concept: Add "The Leader's Sphere" or "Sphere of Influence" logic.

The Text: "In a complex deal, you are rarely the line manager of the people you need to win. You must move them from 'compliance' to 'belief.' GAIN provides the intelligence to align the mission with their own drivers (Achievement/Recognition), so they choose to follow your lead".

The Rationale: This addresses the "Herding Cats" problem in enterprise sales. It validates your Strategic Operator persona by showing you understand command structures (Sphere of Control vs. Sphere of Influence).

3. The "Spectrum" Upgrade (Cognitive Alignment)
We refined the user spectrum to focus on psychological control rather than just skill.

The Change:

Skilled Navigator: Redefined as someone who maintains "Cognitive Alignment," ensuring every AI output mirrors the stakeholder's Epistemology.

Unconscious Drifter: Framed as someone who risks Safety and Order by passively accepting "generic noise".

The Rationale: This appeals to the Power driver. It frames the use of GAIN not as a "shortcut," but as a way to maintain tighter Narrative Lock on the deal.

4. The "Anti-Agentic" Subtitle
The Change: Add the subtitle: "Because you can't automate a belief system.".

The Rationale: This is the core philosophical argument against full automation (Autonomous Agents). It aligns with the "British Intelligence" theme: "If you don't know your beliefs, you're pissing up a wall".

5. The "Chat Handoff" Prompt Update
The Change: Emphasize the [PASTE YOUR ADDITIONAL CONTEXT HERE] placeholder as the critical "Human Injection" point.

The Rationale: This is the technical mechanism for preventing Intelligence Decay. It proves that the "Human in the Loop" is active, feeding personal observations (HUMINT) back into the system to keep it accurate.

